<div id="ta101_1" class="block" style="display:block"><p>
First of all you have to divide the dialogue into chunks forming the subtitles. 
</p>
<p>
While watching your multimedia file, mark on the script with a pencil the points you think are suitable to cue in new subtitles. Normally these points refer to pauses in the dialogue.
</p>
<p>
If you don&#39;t have the script, it is worthwile to transcrbe the dialogue yourself as an aid to spotting the subtitles.
</p>
